/*
:name: abc_mathops
:type: lgraph compile
*/

// Flat combinational fixture for the pass.abc multiplier / right-shift bit-blast
// and the division blackbox (task 2a-abc follow-on). No hierarchy and no
// narrowing, so the design stays a clean combinational cone that `pass color
// acyclic` colors in full (synth coloring deliberately excludes mult/div as
// region seeds; acyclic does not, so every arithmetic op lands in a region and
// is exercised end-to-end). Covers:
//   * mult   : unsigned `a*b`, signed `c*e`, and an n-ary `a*b*a`
//              (array multiplier; the partial-product adds use pass.abc.adder)
//   * sra    : logical `a>>n` (unsigned operand) and arithmetic `c>>n` (signed)
//   * div    : unsigned `a/b`, signed equal-width `c/e`, and signed `cw/e` with a
//              divisor (e:s4) NARROWER than the dividend (cw:s8) — BLACKBOXED
//              (kept native), so a `div-blackbox` warning fires and the divider is
//              not tech-mapped. The narrower-signed-operand case exercises the
//              blackbox read-back's operand-sign preservation (the LEC fit()s a
//              Div operand by sign, so dropping it would zero- instead of
//              sign-extend the divisor and diverge for negatives).
//
// Widths are deliberately small (u4/s4, n:u2): the cvc5 LEC of a bit-blasted
// array multiplier scales steeply with operand width, and these widths still
// exercise every feature/plumbing path above. The exhaustive multiplier/shifter
// math over wider operands is proven separately by //pass/abc:abc_arith_test.
mod abc_mathops(a:u4, b:u4, c:s4, e:s4, cw:s8, n:u2) -> (mul:u8@[0], muls:s8@[0], mul3:u12@[0],
                                                          srl:u4@[0], sra:s4@[0],
                                                          dv:u4@[0], dvs:s4@[0], dwide:s8@[0]) {
  mul   = a * b
  muls  = c * e
  mul3  = a * b * a
  srl   = a >> n
  sra   = c >> n
  dv    = a / b
  dvs   = c / e
  dwide = cw / e
}
